Amanda Khoza, News24 Durban – A speedster was on Monday fined R40 000 and had his driver’s licence suspended for twelve months at the Hibberdene Magistrate's Court in KwaZulu-Natal. Road Traffic Inspectorate chief provincial inspector Aboo Aboobaker said the man was nabbed at around 9:10 on December 16 clocking 223km/h. The 28-year-old was driving a C63 AMG Mercedes Benz when he was arrested on the N2 in Ifafa.      24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  